        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(codex): require admin for native controls",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n### What Problem This Solves\n\nSensitive native Codex controls did not consistently consume the owner/admin authorization facts already available to the command and bound-conversation paths.\n\n### Why This Change Was Made\n\nNative execution and binding mutation should follow the existing privileged-control boundary while read-only status, help, and invalid-usage responses remain available.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Rebase onto merged #97955 and reuse its canonical `canMutateCodexHost` owner-or-`operator.admin` predicate.\n- Preserve #97955's `/codex computer-use install` authorization and documentation unchanged.\n- Require current owner identity or `operator.admin` scope for native Codex execution, control, binding, and detach operations.\n- Recheck current sender authority before every bound Codex turn.\n- Return an explicit owner/admin denial for blocked bound turns.\n- Carry current owner and Gateway-scope facts through the generic inbound-claim event.\n- Document the native-control authorization boundary.\n- Add regression coverage for denied side effects, owner/admin allowance, current-sender propagation, visible denial, and read-only status access.\n\n## Validation\n\n### Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/codex/src/commands.test.ts extensions/codex/src/conversation-binding.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts` — 3 files, 381 tests passed.\n- `node scripts/check-src-extension-import-boundary.mjs --json` — no violations.\n- `node scripts/check-sdk-package-extension-import-boundary.mjs --json` — no violations.\n- `node scripts/check-test-helper-extension-import-boundary.mjs --json` — no violations.\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check ...` for touched source, tests, and docs — passed.\n- `node scripts/check-docs-mdx.mjs docs README.md` — 685 files passed.\n- `node scripts/docs-link-audit.mjs` — 5,493 internal links checked, zero broken.\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` — passed.\n- Structured Codex autoreview against merged `upstream/main` — clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Existing real stdio child-process proof remains attached with its original proof SHA and current-head alignment notes.\n\n## Notes\n\n### User Impact\n\nOwners and `operator.admin` callers retain native Codex control. Ordinary command-authorized senders can still use read-only/status surfaces but cannot start, mutate, detach, or drive native Codex execution. Blocked bound turns now explain the owner/admin requirement.\n\n`pnpm docs:list` was attempted but pnpm aborted an interactive modules-directory reconciliation in the non-TTY checkout. The underlying MDX and link checks were run directly and passed.\n\nAI-assisted change; I reviewed the implementation and validation results.",
